{"title":"Unintended Consequences","link":"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/905135945/0/marginalrevolution~Unintended-Consequences.html","date":1727176640000,"content":"<p>Courtesy of MRU here are two new econ-practice games on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://practice.mru.org/negative/\">negative externalities</a> and <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://practice.mru.org/positive/\">positive externalities</a>. Great for students.</p>\r\n<p>But don’t forget that if you are not careful regulation can often lead to <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolutionuniversity.typeform.com/to/nIvYSGLk?typeform-source=practice.mru.org\">Unintended Consequences</a> (a fun choose your adventure story!)</p>\r\n<p>All of these resources are free for any teacher of economics but, of course, they go great with the best principles of economics textbook, <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://www.macmillanlearning.com/college/us/product/Modern-Principles-of-Economics/p/1319421237?\">Modern Principles of Economics</a>!</p>\r\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com/marginalrevolution/2024/09/unintended-consequences.html\">Unintended Consequences</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/t/0/0/marginalrevolution/~https://marginalrevolution.com\">Marginal REVOLUTION</a>.</p>\r\n<img height=\"1\" width=\"1\" src=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/~/i/905135945/0/marginalrevolution\" />\r\n<div><a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/28/905135945/marginalrevolution\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/fblike20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/29/905135945/marginalrevolution,\"><img height=\"20\" src=\"https://assets.feedblitz.com/i/pinterest20.png\" /></a> <a href=\"https://feeds.feedblitz.com/_/24/905135945/mar